title: For Sale:  OKLAHOMA PRIVATE LAND ELK HUNTS FOR 2017-2018
postcontent:
We are offering hunters the chance to harvest free-ranging elk on our ranch.
Hunts include meals and lodging.
The elk found on our ranch are free ranging descendants of those released in the Wichita Wildlife Refuge in the early 1900's by proclamation of Teddy Roosevelt. These are the same elk that hunters wait a lifetime to draw a tag for in the refuge which is only 11 miles as the crow flies from our ranch.
There's no need to drive all the way to New Mexico or Colorado as we are nestled in the Wichita Mountains in Kiowa county Oklahoma which is only 200 miles from Fort Worth, an easy 4 - 4.5 hour drive and only 2 hours from Oklahoma City.
I have a well concealed 2 person ladder stand and an established ground blind set up for a 30-50 yard shot, or you can pick a spot of your own choosing. Rifle shots can range anywhere from 30 yards out to 400 yards and beyond.
This is a fair chase hunt for free ranging animals - not a high fenced canned hunt. Therefore you must rely on your cunning and abilities to bag one of these amazing animals. This is real hunting and as such there is no guarantee that you will fill your tag but we ensure feed is available to them year-round and there are several bulls, cows and calves making regular visits.
All game regulations will be adhered to and a contract must be signed and notarized.
Those who have a lifetime license are not required to purchase an elk tag, however annual license holders and nonresidents must purchase an elk tag.
According to the Oklahoma wildlife regulations, legal bulls in our special southwest zone must have at least 5 points on at least one side and an antlerless elk is defined as any elk with no visible antlers, regardless of sex.
